@astrofrog - Do you have time to finish this PR soon?

From my side, the only key point is that travis-ci passes.
I think we'll have changes / follow-up PRs in the coming months any ways, as people start using this for their work, and the best way to get good feedback is to put it in `master` or even to make a new release.

@bsipocz - I've removed the redundant travis-ci build you mentioned.

@astrofrog - I've added back Python 2.6 on travis-ci and listed it in the supported Python versions in `setup.py`.

I've had (admittedly very few) real issues only surface on Python 2.6 in Astropy and Gammapy, and it takes some build time on travis-ci ... that was my motivation for suggesting to drop support for it now.
But OK ... if you think there's users that need to run it on 2.6 (i.e. there's any value in supporting it for `photutils 0.2`), let's keep Python 2.6 support.

@yselivonchyk The protobuf requirement comes upstream from ONNX. I recommend that you use conda to install protobuf. You might find you need to pin a specific version and/or remove previous installations of protobuf to get things to work properly.
You can refer to [the ONNX instructions](https://github.com/onnx/onnx) which state conda is the primary route, but you can also build from source if you don't want to use conda.
Brew is not mentioned in their docs nor ours, and I believe this is because you can really tangle up your protobuf install with brew. But if you're a brew master, then please let us know how you solved it with brew.

