Since the use of the Right stream is rather limited there is no helper function to retrieve it. You can, however, iterate over the frameset and distinguish "Right" IR using the `stream_index`. Something like:
```cpp
auto frameset = pipe.wait_for_frames();
rs2::frame right;
for (auto&& frame : frameset)
{
    if (frame.get_profile().stream_index() == RS2_STREAM_INFRARED &&
        frame.get_profile().stream_index() == 2)
    {
         right = frame;
    }
}
return right.as<rs2::video_frame>();
```

